# Project Rules: Event Maple

<i18n_strategy>
  ## Internationalization (i18n) with next-intl
  - **Library**: Use `next-intl` exclusively. No other i18n libraries allowed.
  - **Structure**: All routes must be under `/app/[locale]/...`.
  - **Locales**: Default English (`en`), Others: Spanish (`es`), Portuguese (`pt`), French (`fr`).
  - **Middleware**: Use `next-intl` middleware for locale detection and redirection.
</i18n_strategy>

<translation_management>
  ## Translation Management (JSON)
  - **Location**: `messages/{locale}.json`.
  - **No Hardcoding**: NEVER write visible text directly in `.tsx` files. ALWAYS use `useTranslations`.
  - **Organization**: Nest keys by feature/page (e.g., `HomePage.title`, `Events.card.button`).
  
  ## Component Workflow
  - **CRITICAL**: Every time a new component is created or an existing one is edited, ALWAYS verify i18n compliance.
  - **Immediate Action**: Extract any new text to the corresponding `messages/{locale}.json` files immediately.
  - **Verification**: Ensure no "hardcoded" strings remain in the rendered output.
</translation_management>

<seo_guidelines>
  ## SEO & Metadata
  - **Hreflang**: Implement `alternates` in [generateMetadata](cci:1://file:///home/botom/Projects/Personal/event-planner/app/%28dashboard%29/events/%5BeventId%5D/page.tsx:18:0-58:1) for all supported locales.
  - **Canonicals**: Canonical URL must match the current locale.
  - **Root**: Root `/` must redirect (307) to the detected locale without rendering duplicate content.
  - **Sitemap**: Generate dynamic routes for all locales in [sitemap.ts](cci:7://file:///home/botom/Projects/Personal/event-planner/app/sitemap.ts:0:0-0:0).
</seo_guidelines>

<development_standards>
  ## Navigation
  - **Link Component**: Use `Link` from `@/i18n/navigation` (wrapper), NOT `next/link`.
  - **Redirects**: Use `redirect` from `@/i18n/navigation`.
  
  ## Components
  - **Server Components**: Prefer `await getTranslations` here for better performance.
  - **Client Components**: Use `useTranslations` and provide messages via `NextIntlClientProvider`.
  
  ## Database (Supabase)
  - Maintain current structure for dynamic content (events) for now.
  - Future: Localized columns in DB (e.g., `description_en`).
</development_standards>